<paragraph id="8BD436C2871CAA0346A0FBA6D85EAEFB" blockId="7.[189,1399,1108,1246]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
This species was described based on two male specimens collected by Francisco Campos Ribadeneira in Posorja (“Posoya”), 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652871CAA0347D0FB8BD951AEB6" box="[461,561,1145,1171]" name="Ecuador" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. Campos (
<date id="FFD51002871CAA0344B0FB8BD854AEB6" box="[685,820,1145,1171]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1878" valueMax="1943">1878–1943</date>
) was an intellectual from Guayaquil and the first Ecuadorian entomologist (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33871CAA0347E5FB6CD998AE9D" author="Barragan" box="[504,760,1182,1208]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Barragan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="410 - 423" refId="ref19183" refString="Barragan A. R., Dangles O., Cardenas R. E. &amp; Onore G. 2009. The history of entomology in Ecuador. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (n. s.) 45: 410 - 423. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2009.10697626" type="journal article" year="2009">
Barragán 
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0871CAA03446DFB6DD9CEAE9D" box="[624,686,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). He collected numerous insects and created the first entomological collection in that country (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33871CAA0344BCFB31D852AEFB" author="Moret" box="[673,818,1219,1246]" firstAuthor="Moret" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref21267" refString="Moret P. 2005. Los coleopteros Carabidae del paramo en los Andes del Ecuador. Sistematica, ecologia y biogeografia. Museo de Zoologia, Centro de Biodiversidad y Ambiente, Escuela de Biologia. Pontificia Universidad Catolica del Ecuador, Quito." type="book" year="2005">Moret 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD436C2871CAA0C46A0FAF4DA52AB69" blockId="7.[189,1399,1286,1423]" lastBlockId="8.[189,1399,267,332]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
One of those males was found at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07871CAA034427FAF4D9F4AF05" box="[570,660,1286,1312]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
under the number 24881 and bears an original Cockerell’s label of 
<typeStatus id="54D08860871CAA0346C0FAD9DA73AF60" box="[221,275,1323,1349]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
. The specimen (
<figureCitation id="13502A47871CAA0347CFFAD9D978AF60" box="[466,536,1323,1349]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1468,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[189,1398,1468,1923]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Centris disclusa Cockerell, 1922, holotype, ♂ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534192). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722958" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722958/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) has the following data label: Posorja Ecua FCamposR [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41871CAA03433DFAD9DA3DAF4C" authority="Ckll" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disclusa">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0871CAA03433DFAD9DA7DAF4C" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Centris disclusa</emphasis>
Ckll
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="54D08860871CAA034775FAA2DAC6AF4F" box="[360,422,1360,1386]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Type</typeStatus>
